(43, 7, 28, 40, 11, 27, 27, 'ye know not', 'Knowledge of the Father and Son', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and the Father, highlighting that true knowledge of God comes through the Son. Jesus asserts that while people may know him, they do not know the Father, which parallels the idea in Matthew that only the Son reveals the Father.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 28, 62, 2, 3, 4, NULL, 'Knowledge of God and Commandments', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of knowing God and the implications of that knowledge. John 7:28 highlights that true knowledge of God comes from recognizing the one who is sent, while 1 John 2:3-4 asserts that knowing Him is evidenced by keeping His commandments.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 28, 9, 2, 12, 12, 'ye know not', 'Knowledge of God', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of knowing God. In John 7:28, Jesus states that the people do not know the one who sent him, paralleling 1 Samuel 2:12, where Eli''s sons are described as not knowing the Lord.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 28, 19, 9, 10, 10, NULL, 'Knowledge and Trust in God', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowing God and trusting Him. In both passages, knowing God is linked to a relationship of trust and reliance on Him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 29, 43, 8, 55, 55, 'I know him', 'Knowledge of God Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the speaker''s knowledge of God. In John 7:29, the speaker asserts, ''I know him,'' which is echoed in John 8:55, reinforcing the theme of true knowledge of God versus ignorance.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 29, 40, 11, 27, 27, 'I am from him', 'Knowledge of the Father and Son', 'This connection highlights the intimate relationship between the Father and the Son. Both passages emphasize the unique knowledge that the Son has of the Father, as well as the Son''s role in revealing the Father to others.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 29, 43, 1, 18, 18, 'I am from him', 'Connection of Divine Knowledge', 'This connection highlights the relationship between Jesus and God. Both passages emphasize that Jesus is sent by God and reveals Him to humanity.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 29, 62, 4, 9, 9, 'I am from him', 'Connection of Divine Sending', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being sent by God. In John 7:29, the speaker asserts, ''I am from him,'' while 1 John 4:9 states that God ''sent his only begotten Son.'' This connection highlights the divine mission of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 29, 62, 1, 2, 2, 'I am from him', 'Connection of Manifestation and Origin', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine origin and manifestation. Both passages emphasize the relationship between the speaker and the Father, indicating a direct link to eternal life.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 30, 43, 7, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Timing in John', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of timing, with Jesus stating that ''my time is not yet come'' in John 7:6, and later indicating that ''his hour was not yet come'' in John 7:30. This connection highlights the significance of divine timing in Jesus'' ministry.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 30, 43, 8, 20, 20, NULL, 'Connection of Jesus'' Protection', 'Both passages emphasize that no man laid hands on Jesus because his hour was not yet come. This connection highlights the divine timing and protection surrounding Jesus during his ministry.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 30, 19, 76, 10, 10, 'no man laid hands on him', 'Divine Restraint of Wrath', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine control over human actions. In John 7:30, the phrase ''no man laid hands on him'' suggests that despite human intent, God''s timing prevails, paralleling Psalms 76:10''s idea that ''the remainder of wrath shalt thou restrain.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 30, 23, 46, 10, 10, NULL, 'Divine Timing and Purpose', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine timing, as seen in John 7:30 where ''his hour was not yet come,'' and Isaiah 46:10, which emphasizes God''s sovereignty in declaring events from the beginning. Both passages underscore that God''s plans unfold according to His counsel.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 30, 40, 21, 46, 46, NULL, 'Fear of the Multitude', 'Both passages emphasize the fear of the multitude when seeking to lay hands on Jesus. In John, the reason for not laying hands on him is his hour not yet coming, while in Matthew, they feared the multitude because they viewed him as a prophet.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 30, 41, 11, 18, 18, 'sought to take him', 'Attempts to Harm Jesus', 'This connection highlights the ongoing attempts to take or destroy Jesus. Both passages emphasize the hostility from religious leaders towards him, indicating a growing tension as they sought to act against him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 30, 42, 13, 32, 33, 'his hour was not yet come', 'Timing of Jesus'' Mission', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' appointed time for action. Both passages emphasize that Jesus'' mission unfolds according to a divine schedule, as seen in ''his hour was not yet come'' and ''for it cannot be that a prophet perish out of Jerusalem.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 31, 43, 12, 42, 42, 'believed on him', 'Belief Amidst Fear of Rejection', 'Both passages emphasize belief in Jesus despite external pressures. In John 7:31, people wonder about the miracles of Christ, while John 12:42 shows that some believed but feared social consequences, highlighting a theme of belief challenged by societal rejection.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 31, 40, 12, 23, 23, 'more miracles than these which this man hath done', 'Recognition of Jesus'' Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the people''s recognition of Jesus'' miraculous works and his potential messianic identity. In John 7:31, the people question if the Christ will perform greater miracles, while in Matthew 12:23, they acknowledge him as the ''son of David,'' a title associated with the Messiah.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 31, 43, 8, 30, 32, NULL, 'Belief and Discipleship Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief in Jesus. Both passages emphasize the response of the people to Jesus'' words and miracles, leading to a call for continued faith and discipleship.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 31, 44, 8, 13, 13, 'more miracles than these which this man hath done', 'Belief in Miracles', 'Both passages emphasize belief in Christ based on miracles. In John, people question if the Messiah will perform greater miracles, while in Acts, Simon believes after witnessing the miracles done by Philip.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 31, 40, 11, 3, 6, 'more miracles than these which this man hath done', 'Connection of Miracles and Belief', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief in Jesus as the Messiah based on his miracles. Both passages emphasize the expectation of the Messiah performing miraculous deeds, as seen in the question about whether Christ will do more miracles and the miracles Jesus references in response to John.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 31, 42, 8, 13, 13, 'believed on him', 'Belief and Temptation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief in both passages. In John 7:31, people express belief in Jesus'' miracles, while in Luke 8:13, some initially believe but later fall away during temptation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 31, 59, 2, 26, 26, 'believed on him', 'Connection of Faith and Works', 'This connection highlights the relationship between belief and action. In John 7:31, the people''s faith in Christ is questioned, while James 2:26 emphasizes that faith must be accompanied by works to be alive.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
