(43, 7, 32, 42, 22, 52, 53, 'the Pharisees and the chief priests', 'Authority and Arrest of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the actions of the Pharisees and chief priests in both passages. In John 7:32, they send officers to take Jesus, while in Luke 22:52-53, Jesus confronts them as they come to arrest him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 7, 32, 43, 7, 45, 53, 'the Pharisees and the chief priests sent officers', 'Response to Pharisees'' Orders', 'This connection highlights the response of the officers sent by the Pharisees, who report back that ''Never man spake like this man.'' Both passages emphasize the tension between the Pharisees'' authority and the compelling nature of Jesus'' words.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
